SETS: 2-3

Legs!!! They’ve always been my favorite body part to train. Follow me as I put you through a leg-cardio routine, body weight only with plyometrics. This one is suppose to be fun, well, at least for the first round - gimme 3 rounds, and we’ll talk later! 

1. Alt. Lateral Lunge with Skip
2. Front Lunge to High Knee
3. Squat Jump Variation
4. Reverse Lunge Skip
5. Low Squat Thrust

REST: 1 min between each set

5 movements you don’t need to be on your feet to do, hence why I’m telling you to hit the ground 😎 but grab those dumbbells. We’ll target CORE, GLUTES, SHOULDERS, BACK & BICEPS. Yup, all that in 5 moves. You’re looking at a 6 minute set, and you’ll do just 3 - that’s a 20min challenge you can do during commercial breaks!

1. Core + Glutes: Hydrants
2. Core + Back: Beast Row
3. Core + Shoulders: Seated Press + Heel Tap
4. Core + Shoulders: Low Plank Tap
5. Core + Biceps: Russian Twist w/Pike

REST: 1 min between each set

Equipment: a pair of dumbbells, 10-20lbs

node.text:
#Selfcare is a lot of things, yes. But more than ever we need to be reminded that self care is THIS!

Don’t waste your time, energy and peace engaging with those that aren’t aligned with you. I’ve always considered myself an open minded person, never voided or neglected those that disagree with me, but my God, I’ve absolutely learned that I do not need to engage with those so adamant about imposing their views so strongly that it becomes clear that their only intent is to convince me that they are right and I am wrong. Ugh, what low vibrations this pulls me into. Leave it alone, let them be.

Remember, what is forced, is against nature and therefore is against all truth.

Save your peace 💜
